6:
Keh-heh! What was that, li'l lady?
Yer gonna have to speak up if yer tryna
call fer help!
9:
Not that there's anyone around here
to come help ya anyway!
11:
That's what you think! Lassie, nautical
warrior of justice, is here to save
the day!
17:
Listen up, baddies! How about you
leave that poor girl alone and pick on
someone your own size!
20:
Who's this brat supposed to be?
You don't want any of this, little lady!
23:
Grr... I'm not a brat!
I'll overlook your transgression...
27:
But ONLY if you let that poor woman go!
You still have time to make things right!
29:
And time to cleanse your hands of these
crooked ways! And time for you to start
life anew—on the straight and narrow!
31:
Oho! Such mercy from a guardian angel
of justice! Here's the thing though,
pipsqueak...
40:
Easy there... One false move and my
buddy's knife might just go
stabby-stabby.
53:
What's the matter, little justice sailor?
Where's all that bravado from before?
60: The hell do you think yer doin' to—
65:
What're you doin' fightin' in a place like
this? You look like a mess.
70:
I... I had them just where I wanted!
W-way to steal my spotlight!
73:
But, um... I should thank you for helping
anyway, I guess.
77:
A-are you okay, miss? I can't thank you
enough for coming to my rescue.
80:
Oh, don't mention it, ma'am!
Just doing my job!
82: Thank you... Thank you so very much.
85:
Don't be so naive next time. Words won't
get through with some people.
86:
Skip the monologue and just beat the
crap out of 'em, got it?
91:
No way! The path to redemption is open
to anyone willing—nobody's
THAT heartless!
93:
If I just beat them up, how will they ever
get the chance to repent?
96:
Even if it means puttin' yourself
in harm's way?
102:
Ridiculous. Although... the world would
be a better place with more people
like you.
106:
Hee hee! Just doing my part in the
name of nautical justice!
109:
*sigh* That's fine and all, but try not to
pick fights you're not equipped to
handle, okay?
112:
Hmph! Size doesn't matter when it
comes to meting out justice!
116:
I'm gonna keep doing my thing no
matter what anybody says!
119:
Hmm... You know what? I can respect
that kind of determination.
